cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories as it deals with deep neural networks and their compression for image classification tasks. It also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of pruning and quantization techniques could place it in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category, while the framework proposed could be considered a data structure (cs.DS) for compressed neural networks.
